observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

(18) identify the Government’s Shares included in the ending balance of the Due to GSIS, Due to HDMF and Due to Philhealth accounts as of December 31, 2019;

(19) prepare the necessary journal entry to correct the errors, and;

(20) use the correct accounting entries in recording salaries, allowances and deductions of regular employees and the remittances of monthly premium contributions including LGU’s share.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

(26) create a Committee which will update the rates of taxes and fees provided in the current Tax Ordinance to maximize the income generation capabilities of the LGU;

(27) recommend to the Sangguniang Bayan for approval any proposed revisions on the Tax Ordinance;

(28) require the Municipal Treasurer to update the existing Contracts of Lease to conform with the approved revisions on the Tax Ordinance of the LGU;

(29) require each stallholder to sign a Contract of Lease upon application as basis for the collection of rentals.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, through the Municipality’s HRMO:

(32) fill up the vacant positions in the LGU plantilla in accordance with CSC rules and regulations, subject to Personnel Services limitations; 

(33) reduce the number of Job Order Workers so that the functions of the existing regular employees are not duplicated by the JOs; 

 (34) stop the issuance of cash tickets through Job Orders; 

(35) pay the mandated daily minimum wage prescribed by the RTWPB for Region VIII, and;

(36) attach the corresponding copies of Contract of Service of Job Order personnel on their first month of service.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
identify the Government’s Shares included in the ending balance of the Due to GSIS, Due to HDMF and Due to Philhealth accounts as of December 31, 2019;
prepare the necessary journal entry to correct the errors, and;
use the correct accounting entries in recording salaries, allowances and deductions of regular employees and the remittances of monthly premium contributions including LGU’s share.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
create a Committee which will update the rates of taxes and fees provided in the current Tax Ordinance to maximize the income generation capabilities of the LGU;
recommend to the Sangguniang Bayan for approval any proposed revisions on the Tax Ordinance;
require the Municipal Treasurer to update the existing Contracts of Lease to conform with the approved revisions on the Tax Ordinance of the LGU;
require each stallholder to sign a Contract of Lease upon application as basis for the collection of rentals.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, through the Municipality’s HRMO:
fill up the vacant positions in the LGU plantilla in accordance with CSC rules and regulations, subject to Personnel Services limitations;
Reduce the number of Job Order Workers so that the functions of the existing regular employees are not duplicated by the JOs;
stop the issuance of cash tickets through Job Orders;
pay the mandated daily minimum wage prescribed by the RTWPB for Region VIII, and;
attach the corresponding copies of Contract of Service of Job Order personnel on their first month of service.
We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant review the computations in the Job Order payrolls to avoid discrepancies and ensure the use of correct daily wage rates.
